    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3846905297" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3846905297" />
    <a title="David M" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/43332343-david-m"><img alt="David M" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1570428545p2/43332343.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3846905297?book_show_action=true">Feb 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="David M" class="user" itemprop="url" name="David M" href="/user/show/43332343-david-m">David M</a>
      </span>

          added it


          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780934868075" href="/book/show/526627.Society_of_the_Spectacle">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3846905297" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1727049995280474964">Finally got around to reading this book. I was afraid it would seem horribly dated, but in fact not at all. In my opinion, large segments of the left have dropped the ball this past year, but Debord is a Marxist who makes me hesitate to throw the baby out with the bathwater.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


