<div id="review_2984077469" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2984077469" />
    <a title="George" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12187924-george"><img alt="George" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1345839087p2/12187924.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2984077469?book_show_action=true">Oct 06, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="George" class="user" itemprop="url" name="George" href="/user/show/12187924-george">George</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2984077469" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5643882073171400660">A very difficult book to read. Lots of re-reads and focus and translations if you are not a native English speaker. But very rewarding! I found myself lost so many times but when you remove the words that are used to emphasize the message, you will find yourself saying what is actually happening to us. <br/><br/>A new project is underway. The spectacle! The spectacle supported by capitalism tends to overwrite our own history and place new foundations. That is shocking. Ultimately the message is that the s</span>
  <span id="freeText5643882073171400660" style="display:none">A very difficult book to read. Lots of re-reads and focus and translations if you are not a native English speaker. But very rewarding! I found myself lost so many times but when you remove the words that are used to emphasize the message, you will find yourself saying what is actually happening to us. <br /><br />A new project is underway. The spectacle! The spectacle supported by capitalism tends to overwrite our own history and place new foundations. That is shocking. Ultimately the message is that the spectacle industry consumes people, history and the future, removing all the links and variables from the past and diminishing the people's relationships and communication. <br /><br />It is a really good book that explores the spectacle from every possible angle.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5643882073171400660" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
