        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer268521201" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5741899444154161760">It&apos;s quite short (at only 150 or so pages) but it ain&apos;t snappy - Debord manages to excoriate ideology, alienation, much of the Old Left, almost all of the New Left and provide us with a circuitous and at times dense analysis of the emerging consumer society of the late 20th century. I keep coming back to it, and I keep finding turns of phrase and pieces of an argument that make me revisit and revise my political sense of the world around me. A deserved classic.</span>
  <span id="freeText5741899444154161760" style="display:none">It's quite short (at only 150 or so pages) but it ain't snappy - Debord manages to excoriate ideology, alienation, much of the Old Left, almost all of the New Left and provide us with a circuitous and at times dense analysis of the emerging consumer society of the late 20th century. I keep coming back to it, and I keep finding turns of phrase and pieces of an argument that make me revisit and revise my political sense of the world around me. A deserved classic.</span>
